cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.MM, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design and performance of interactive music scenarios.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the control of concurrent execution of objects in a heterogeneous system.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper mentions the use of the Non-deterministic Timed Concurrent Constraint (ntcc) calculus.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper mentions audio and video processing.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper mentions the development of an automatic verifier for ntcc.
